channel.title: How Do I Add 474 Items In My Server?
channel.description: Heey , when i want to spawn in my server '' Black ele' '' shirt, i get ''Null'' how do i add this item, and more items in Server?

item.title: How Do I Add 474 Items In My Server?
item.dc:creator: @my_stoof my stoof
item.description:
@my_stoof wrote:

Most items in 474’s have “Null”

To remove this…

Go into your item.cfg file
Search for the item you want.
You will see something like : Black_Ele_Skirt Null 6000 5000 1000
Remove the “null” so it looks like this Black_Ele_Skirt 6000 5000 1000
Save it and no need to compile.
If you want to make it wearable. Go into Items.java
Search for this

	static final int[] legs = {

Whatever the item code for Black ele skirt is… add it at the end

My current items in my final int[] legs is :

static final int[] legs = { 428, 538, 542, 548, 1011, 1013, 1015, 1033, 1067, 1069, 1071, 1073, 1075, 1077, 1079, 1081, 1083, 1085, 1087, 1089, 1091, 1093, 1095, 1099, 1835, 2493, 2495, 2497, 2585, 2593, 2601, 2609, 2617, 2625, 2655, 2663, 2671, 3059, 3389, 3472, 3473, 3474, 3475, 3476, 3477, 3478, 3479, 3480, 3483, 3485, 3795, 4070, 4087, 4093, 4103, 4113, 4505, 4510, 4585, 4712, 4714, 4722, 4730, 4738, 4751, 4759, 4874, 4875, 4876, 4877, 4898, 4899, 4900, 4901, 4922, 4923, 4924, 4925, 4946, 4947, 4948, 4949, 4970, 4971, 4972, 4973, 4994, 4995, 4996, 4997, 5048, 5050, 5052, 5555, 5576, 6108, 6130, 6135, 6141, 6181, 6185, 6187, 6386, 6390, 6390, 6396, 6404, 6655, 6924, 7386, 7593, 11722, 11726 };

add “,” to the end of the 11726 so it looks like : 11726, and then add the black ele skirt code after so it looks like:

11726, 10402 };

Save it and compile

EDIT:

If you dont have a compiler for your 474. Here take mine
